# .env.test — credentials for integration and E2E tests.
# .env.test is gitignored and will NOT be committed.
#
# ── How to populate ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The easiest way is to run `npm run setup` (or `bash setup/setup.sh`).
# setup.sh writes .env.test automatically, synced to whichever Supabase
# option you chose:
#
#   Option 3 (bundled Docker stack) — .env.test is always written/updated
#     to match docker/.env.docker. Re-run setup if credentials change.
#
#   Options 1 & 2 (Cloud or existing self-hosted) — .env.test is written
#     once if it doesn't exist. Edit values by hand after that.
#
# If you prefer to fill this in manually, copy it to .env.test and set:
#
#   Bundled Docker stack (option 3):
#     SUPABASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#     SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<value from docker/.env.docker>
#     DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:<POSTGRES_PASSWORD>@localhost:5432/flashquery
#
#   Supabase CLI (self-hosted, option 2):
#     SUPABASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#     SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<value from `supabase status`>
#     DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:<password>@localhost:54322/postgres
#
#   Supabase Cloud (option 1):
#     SUPABASE_URL=https://yourproject.supabase.co
#     SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service role key from cloud dashboard>
#     DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:<password>@db.yourproject.supabase.co:5432/postgres
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Required for integration tests
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
DATABASE_URL=

# Required for MCP bearer-token auth (used by the scenario test suite).
# Must match MCP_AUTH_SECRET in .env. setup.sh copies it automatically.
MCP_AUTH_SECRET=

# Required for disk-verify steps in the scenario test suite.
# Must match VAULT_PATH in .env. setup.sh copies it automatically.
VAULT_PATH=

# Required for embedding tests AND LLM directed scenarios (Phase 98+)
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional — only needed for Ollama embedding tests
OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
